**AIRCRAFT BROKER REFERRAL PROGRAM**

Partner with Provenarc Aero Solutions to Accelerate Sales and Increase Client
Satisfaction

Program Overview

Provenarc Aero Solutions partners with aircraft sales brokerages to provide
professional records digitization services that accelerate transactions,
reduce deal friction, and enhance your value proposition to both sellers
and buyers. Our white-glove concierge model means no shipping carriers
are ever used---we pick up and return logbooks directly, eliminating the
risk inherent in mailing irreplaceable documents.

Why Partner with Provenarc Aero Solutions?

Accelerate Deal Cycles

Digital records enable remote pre-buy due diligence. Buyers can review
complete aircraft histories before committing to travel for in-person
inspections. This shortens time-to-close by days or weeks, particularly
for out-of-state buyers or international transactions.

Reduce Transaction Risk

One-third of aircraft transactions are delayed or cancelled due to
maintenance documentation issues. Professional digitization identifies
gaps early, allowing sellers to address issues before the aircraft goes
to market rather than during critical negotiation phases.

Differentiate Your Brokerage

Offering professional digitization as a standard or premium service sets
your brokerage apart from competitors. Sellers appreciate the added
value. Buyers appreciate the transparency. You close more deals at
higher prices.

Zero Operational Overhead

You do not need to invest in scanning equipment, hire specialized staff,
or develop expertise in aviation document archiving. Provenarc Aero Solutions
handles all logistics, scanning, quality control, and delivery. You
simply refer clients and collect revenue.

Three Partnership Models

Provenarc Aero Solutions offers three distinct partnership structures. You select
the model that aligns with your business objectives and client service
philosophy.

Model 1: Standard Referral Commission

**How it works:** You refer clients to Provenarc Aero Solutions. We provide the
service directly to the aircraft owner under our brand. You receive a
commission for every completed job.

**Commission structure:**

-   15% of gross revenue on all referrals

-   Paid within 30 days of service completion

-   No minimum volume required

-   Lifetime attribution (if client returns for additional services, you
    continue to earn)

**Example economics:** You refer 10 aircraft per year at an average job
value of \$1,500. Your annual commission: \$2,250.

**Best for:** Brokerages that prefer simplicity, minimal administrative
overhead, and passive income from referrals without client-facing
involvement.

Model 2: White-Label / Co-Branded Service

**How it works:** Provenarc Aero Solutions operates as your invisible back office.
We provide all scanning and digitization services, but your branding
appears on customer-facing materials. You control pricing, client
relationships, and upsell opportunities.

**Wholesale pricing structure:**

-   You pay Provenarc Aero Solutions 60--70% of our standard retail pricing

-   You set your own client-facing price and retain the margin

-   Typical margin: 30--40% of retail pricing

-   SLA guarantees on turnaround times

**Example economics:** Standard Provenarc Aero Solutions retail price for a
single-engine piston transaction package is \$1,500. You pay us \$1,000
(wholesale). You charge the client \$1,500. Your margin: \$500 per job.

**Best for:** Established brokerages with strong brand identity who want
to offer records digitization as a proprietary service without building
internal capability.

Model 3: Volume Partner with Tiered Incentives

**How it works:** For high-volume brokerages handling dozens of
transactions annually, Provenarc Aero Solutions offers tiered commission rates that
increase with volume. Available as either standard referral or
white-label model.

**Tiered commission structure (standard referral model):**

-   Tier 1 (1--10 jobs/year): 15% commission

-   Tier 2 (11--25 jobs/year): 18% commission

-   Tier 3 (26--50 jobs/year): 20% commission

-   Tier 4 (51+ jobs/year): 22% commission

**Tiered wholesale pricing (white-label model):**

-   Tier 1 (1--10 jobs/year): 65% of retail

-   Tier 2 (11--25 jobs/year): 62% of retail

-   Tier 3 (26--50 jobs/year): 60% of retail

-   Tier 4 (51+ jobs/year): 58% of retail

**Example economics:** Mason Amelia Aircraft Sales handles 200+
transactions. At 25% digitization adoption (50 jobs/year), white-label
pricing at 60% of retail yields \$30,000 annual margin opportunity on a
\$75,000 gross revenue stream.

**Best for:** Regional or national brokerages with significant
transaction volume who can drive consistent referral flow.

Services Available to Your Clients

All partnership models provide access to Provenarc Aero Solutions\' complete 14-tier
service menu. The most relevant services for brokerage clients are:

Tier 2: Transaction Ready Package

**Pricing:** \$1,200--\$5,000 depending on aircraft complexity

Comprehensive digitization optimized for aircraft sale. Full OCR
searchable PDF/A, organized folder structure, 48-hour priority
turnaround, hyperlinked table of contents, shareable \"Digital Closing
Packet\" with password protection and time-expiring cloud link. Includes
cover memo summarizing total times, last annual date, and AD compliance
status.

**Typical use case:** Seller engaging your brokerage to list an
aircraft. You offer Transaction Ready package as part of your listing
service. Digitized records posted alongside listing photos accelerate
buyer interest and enable remote due diligence.

Tier 3: Pre-Buy Inspection Support

**Pricing:** \$1,500--\$4,000 depending on aircraft complexity

On-site scanning at inspection facility with same-day to 24-hour
turnaround. Creates searchable digital copy for buyer\'s A&P/IA review.
Includes flagged-items memo identifying documentation gaps: missing
signatures, incomplete AD entries, undocumented 337s, absent 8130-3
forms.

**Typical use case:** Buyer represented by your brokerage scheduling
pre-buy inspection. You coordinate Provenarc Aero Solutions to meet buyer\'s
mechanic at inspection facility. Digitized records allow mechanic to
work from tablet and provide buyer with permanent digital archive
post-purchase.

Tier 14: White-Label Broker Service

**Pricing:** 60--70% of retail pricing (see Model 2 above)

White-label or co-branded scanning service where your branding appears
on all customer-facing deliverables. Provenarc Aero Solutions operates as your
invisible back office. You control client relationships and pricing.
Includes SLA guarantees on turnaround times.

**Typical use case:** Your brokerage markets proprietary records
digitization service under your brand. All client communications come
from you. All deliverables carry your logo. Provenarc Aero Solutions is never
visible to the end client.

Service Level Agreements

Provenarc Aero Solutions commits to the following service standards for all broker
partnership clients:

Turnaround Time Guarantees

-   Single-engine piston (Transaction Ready): 24--48 hours from pickup

-   Twin-engine piston: 3--5 business days from pickup

-   Turboprop/light jet: 5--7 business days from pickup

-   Pre-Buy Inspection Support: Same-day to 24-hour turnaround (on-site)

Quality Standards

-   Minimum 300 DPI scanning resolution for all documents

-   Full optical character recognition (OCR) for text searchability

-   PDF/A archival format for long-term preservation

-   Manual quality control review of every page

-   Zero tolerance for missing pages or out-of-sequence scans

Logistics and Security

-   Concierge pickup and return---no shipping carriers, ever

-   \$100,000 document insurance during transport

-   Encrypted USB delivery (Kingston IronKey 32GB minimum)

-   Secure cloud download with password protection and time-expiring
    links

-   Physical logbooks returned in archival-quality storage boxes

Communication and Transparency

-   Pickup confirmed within 24 hours of request

-   Progress updates at key milestones (pickup complete, scanning in
    progress, QC complete, delivery scheduled)

-   Dedicated broker liaison contact for all partnership inquiries

-   Monthly reporting on job volume, revenue, and commission (if
    applicable)

Marketing Support for Partners

